          <h4>GROSS ANATOMY </h4>
          <p>Gross anatomy is the study of the body's structures that are visible to the naked eye. It's a visual science that includes the study of the form, location, and relationships of body parts.
 </p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
          <img src="microscopic anatomy.jpg">
          <h4>MICROSCOPIC ANATOMY</h4>
          <p>Microscopic anatomy is the study of the structure of cells, tissues, and molecules using a microscope. It's also known as histology. </p>
        </div>

<div class="box">
          <img src="embryology.jpg">
          <h4>EMBRYOLOGY</h4>
          <p>Embryology is the study of how an organism develops from a fertilized egg into an adult. It's a branch of biology that includes the study of fertilization, gametes, and the development of embryos and fetuses. 
<p>      
